node.text: Photo by @navidbaraty / Over the years I’ve photographed various reflections of New York City. I couldn't believe the first time I saw how much of the city can be seen reflected along the sides of glass skyscrapers from high above. It felt as if I'd discovered a sort of hidden dimension that had been there all along, waiting to be noticed. #YourShotPhotographer #NYC

node.text: Photo by Gaanesh Prasad @gp_canon / Toward the end of winter, fire reserves start executing controlled bush back-burning to mitigate the impact of potential naturally occurring bushfires. I captured this frame a few days ago during lockdown while back-burning was happening somewhere in the Blue Mountains. #YourShotPhotographer #Sydney #Australia #BushBackburn

node.text: Photo by Ali Sahi @aliahmedsahi / It was my first international solo travel, and while looking for hotels to stay in Istanbul, I had only one thing in my mind – a place to stay where I can see and capture the magnificent blue mosque from the rooftop or the window. I got my bucket shot and I stayed long at the rooftop, just looking at the Blue Mosque. Istanbul, Turkey. This is an Editor’s Pick chosen from #YourShotPhotographer. Submit your photos for a chance to be featured on the account!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by National Geographic Your Shot on September 05, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and body of water.

node.text: Photo by Navin Kumar @navinvatsa / Many days I crossed this countryside location waterlogged because of heavy rain and flooding during monsoon season. I am documenting the daily lives of people living on either side of this submerged road to highlight the spirit of those facing such difficulties. Almost every year they have to deal with this situation. On this evening, the dark cloud from the north and bright sunlight from the west created a great mood and contrast with the other moving elements, allowing me to capture the difficulties and the human spirit together. #YourShotPhotographer #india

node.text: Photo by Stas Bartnikas @stasbart / Serenity / The Kamchatka Peninsula is one of the few places in the world where untouched nature is preserved. It is possible to travel here by roads that are sparse and unpaved, or only by air in some places. This photo, taken from a helicopter near the Uzon Plateau, depicts a very rare and unspoiled nature that radiates tranquility and serenity. #kamchatka #nature #aerial #YourShotPhotographer
